title: Central Palestine maps, 1917 - 1918
description:
Part 2 Canal, Sinai and Palestine maps, 1914 - 1918


This is a collection of various maps produced during the Great War, 1914 - 1918 to assist the many combatants in the Sinai and Palestine. The sources are British, German and Turkish. These are the maps referred to in the various war diaries of each formation that engaged in combat within this region. Each map has been photographed as a whole map and as individual segments which makes up a very large group of files. The maps have been very useful as a primary historical source in tracing the activities and actions of various forces to within 10 metres of the description
